author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: 'Dhurandhar' continues its reign as 2025's biggest hit, shattering box office records and dominating new releases. The film, starring Ranveer Singh and others, is on a record-breaking spree, aiming to challenge 'Pushpa 2's' domestic net collection. Meanwhile, 'Tu Meri Main Tera Tu Meri' and 'Ikkis' have seen moderate success.
title: 'Dhurandhar' box office: Ranveer, Akshaye starrer crosses Rs 760 crore

author: SUBHASH K JHA
description: Filmmaker Deepa Mehta reflects on her 11-year-old film 'Bollywood Hollywood,' revealing she wrote it in two months as a personal antidote to seriousness. Mehta discusses the casting of Rahul Khanna, Lisa Ray, Moushumi Chatterjee, and Kulbhushan Kharbanda, emphasizing the film's focus on the ironies of NRI life and their emotional ties to India, rather than Bollywood itself.
title: Exclusive | Did you know Deepa Mehta wrote ‘Bollywood Hollywood’ in just two months?

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The 138-year run was broken for the fifth and final Ashes Test against England, with all-rounder Beau Webster included and off-spinner Todd Murphy overlooked.
title: First time in 138 years: Australia field no spinner in SCG Test

author: etimes.in
description: Television actors Jay Bhanushali and Mahhi Vij have confirmed their separation after 14 years of marriage. The couple announced their decision to part ways amicably, emphasizing their commitment to their children, Tara, Khushi, and Rajveer. They stated their intention to remain supportive friends, prioritizing peace and respect.
title: Jay Bhanushali, Mahhi Vij part ways after 14 years of marriage; announce separation

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Elon Musk congratulated President Trump on the capture of Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro and his wife in a swift US military operation. Musk's company, Starlink, will provide free broadband service to Venezuelans until February 3rd, supporting citizens during this transition.
title: Maduro arrested: Elon Musk congratulates Trump; calls it ‘a clear message to evil dictators’

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: 'Matter of deep concern': India reacts to US strikes on Venezuela; urges restraint, calls for dialogue

author: P NAVEEN
description: A young man in Sagar district allegedly died by suicide following a family dispute. His wife, upon discovering his body, reportedly went into shock and subsequently jumped into a nearby well, also losing her life. The couple leaves behind a three-month-old son.
title: MP horror: Husband hangs himself, wife jumps into well after seeing his body

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In a dramatic pre-dawn operation, the US launched airstrikes across Venezuela, leading to explosions in Caracas and the reported capture of President Nicolás Maduro and his wife. President Trump announced their detention, stating they will face narco-terrorism charges in New York. This aggressive military action, unprecedented in decades, follows months of US pressure and accusations against Maduro's government regarding drug trafficking and regional instability.
title: Drugs, oil, illegal immigration: Why Trump ordered Venezuela strikes; what we know so far

author: ANURAG BENDE
description: BJP state chief Ravindra Chavan urged Ajit Pawar to introspect before accusing the BJP of corruption, warning of repercussions. Pawar defended fielding relatives of alleged gangsters in Pune polls, differentiating between criminals and their families. He also accused the BJP-ruled PMC of corruption and poor governance, while BJP leader Navneet Rana cautioned Pawar against overstepping boundaries.
title: 'It will create lot of problems': Maha BJP chief Ravindra Chavan hits back at Ajit Pawar

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: A 25-year-old woman was allegedly raped and brutalized inside an ambulance after accepting a lift in dense fog. Her family claims the two arrested suspects are ambulance workers and seeks financial aid for her extensive medical treatment. The victim sustained severe injuries and is awaiting a test identification parade.
title: Faridabad gangrape: Family says assault happened in ambulance; suspects tied to hospital

author: TOI Education
description: CBSE has issued strict guidelines for Class 10 and 12 practical exams from January 1-14, 2026. Schools must ensure adequate resources, inform students, and use only Board-appointed examiners. Special arrangements are mandated for students with special needs. Marks must be uploaded daily and accurately, with no exemptions for sports participation. Non-compliance risks exam cancellation.
title: CBSE Class 10, 12 Practical exams 2026: Board issues strict guidelines; check notice

author: SAT SINGH
description: Dera Sacha Sauda chief Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, serving sentences for rape and murder, has been granted a 40-day parole. This marks his 15th release from Sunaria Jail, Rohtak, since his 2017 conviction. He will spend his parole period at the Dera headquarters in Sirsa.
title: Gurmeet Ram Rahim granted 40-day parole, will remain at Sirsa headquarters

author: KARISHMA KOTWAL
description: Tragedy struck Bhagirathpura as 10 residents died from contaminated drinking water, with locals blaming a police outpost toilet built without a proper septic tank. Sewage reportedly seeped into the water pipeline, leading to the fatal contamination. Residents are demanding culpable homicide charges against those responsible for this grave negligence.
title: 'Negligence in construction': Police loo leak suspected in Indore water tragedy; questions mount

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Starlink is offering free broadband service in Venezuela until February 3, following a US military operation that captured President Nicolas Maduro and First Lady Cilia Flores. Elon Musk expressed support for the people of Venezuela and congratulated President Trump on the arrest, calling it a win for the world.
title: US-Venezuela conflict: Starlink announces free internet service in Venezuela; Elon Musk shares post

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Warren Buffett and the late Charlie Munger finally ended their decades-long regret by acquiring a $4.3 billion stake in Alphabet, Google's parent company, in Q3 2025. This move, driven by firsthand experience of Google's advertising prowess through GEICO, signals Berkshire Hathaway's growing confidence in Alphabet's AI ambitions and its core search business.
title: Warren Buffett's biggest tech regret: Missing Google's IPO; Finally invests after 21 years

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Several people are feared dead following a massive rock collapse at a stone quarry in Odisha's Dhenkanal district on Saturday evening. The incident occurred during drilling and stone exploration, trapping workers under debris. Rescue operations are underway with multiple teams deployed to the site.
title: Odisha rock collapse: Several people feared dead, rescue operation underway

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: Space junk poses a growing threat to vital satellite services. Scientists at CU Boulder are developing an electrostatic tractor beam, a non-contact technology that gently nudges debris to de-orbit. This innovative approach, inspired by science fiction but grounded in physics, offers a safer and more efficient alternative to traditional cleanup methods, potentially revolutionizing orbital debris management.
title: This space technology change how we manage Earth’s orbit

author: RAHUL SINGH
description: A five-year-old girl was abducted, gang-raped, and then thrown from a third-floor building in Bulandshahr, allegedly by two men. The accused, who were reportedly drinking at the time, attempted to stage the incident as an accident.
title: UP horror: 5-year old girl dies after she was raped, thrown from 3rd floor

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US forces conducted a large-scale strike in Venezuela, capturing President Nicolás Maduro and his wife, Cilia Flores, following pre-dawn attacks on Caracas. Maduro faces terrorism and drug charges in New York, with the US accusing him of leading a narco-terrorist organization. The operation's legality is debated, with experts citing potential violations of international law.
title: US strikes in Venezuela: Did Trump have authority to capture Maduro? What the law says

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Hundreds of two-wheelers were destroyed in a massive fire at the Thrissur railway station's paid parking area on Sunday morning. The blaze, suspected to have started from a fallen electric line igniting a covered bike, gutted most of the approximately 400 vehicles. Firefighters brought the flames under control, preventing spread to station platforms.
title: Watch: Fire erupts at Thrissur railway station; hundreds of two-wheelers gutted in blaze

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Venezuela entered a period of uncertainty after President Nicolás Maduro was captured during a US military operation. With no immediate political transition announced, the Supreme Court ordered Vice President Delcy Rodríguez to step in as interim president. Rodríguez condemned the US action, demanded Maduro’s release, and insisted he remains the country’s legitimate leader, even as she took charge of government functions alongside senior ministers and military officials.
title: Who is Delcy Rodriguez? Venezuelan leader named interim president after Maduro’s capture

author: PRIYANKA KAKODKAR, PRADEEP GUPTA, MANOJ BADGERI
description: A significant number of Mahayuti candidates secured unopposed victories in municipal polls, with the BJP leading the count. Opposition leaders decried the situation, alleging widespread use of money and threats to force withdrawals, and accused the state election commission of bias. Allegations of bribery and undue influence were prominent.
title: ‘Why only Mahayuti?’: Oppn slams 68 unopposed Maha civic wins; alleges bribery, threats

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Police state no VIP was involved in the Ankita Bhandari murder case. A man named Dharmendra Kumar was identified as a friend, not a VIP. New allegations suggest a 'Gattu', a top BJP leader, is involved. The Uttarakhand government is open to investigation with credible evidence.
title: Ankita Bhandari murder case: No ‘VIP’ involved, says Haridwar SP; opposition demands CBI probe

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former Australian cricketer Damien Martyn, who was recently hospitalised with meningitis and placed in an induced coma, is now on the road to recovery. His family expressed gratitude to hospital staff, confirming his "progressing well." Martyn, a 54-year-old former batter, had a distinguished career, including two World Cup wins and 13 Test centuries.
title: Damien Martyn health update: Family shares big news on hospitalised Aussie cricketer

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Railway Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw unveiled the new Vande Bharat sleeper train, promising enhanced comfort for overnight journeys with upgraded amenities like improved suspension and modern washrooms.  The first service, connecting Guwahati and Kolkata, is set to launch in January 2026, with fares starting at Rs 2,300.
title: New seats, modern washrooms & more — Here's how Vande Bharat Sleeper looks from inside!

author: TOI Education
description: A Supreme Court safety order on stray dogs in institutional areas set off a chain of circulars: Ministry, CBSE, then Delhi DoE. Social media then twisted “nodal officer” coordination into a false “teachers counting dogs” claim, prompting police action and a teacher’s suspension. Mumbai teachers resisted similar nodal roles. The bigger fight isn’t dogs—it’s non-teaching duties and accountability.
title: The stray-dog row that put school teachers on the hook; here's why they're pushing back

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi's air quality remained in the 'poor' category with an AQI of 298 on Sunday, causing breathing discomfort. Several areas recorded 'very poor' air, while fog impacted flight operations. Authorities urge adherence to GRAP guidelines despite Stage-III restrictions being revoked.
title: Delhi AQI ‘poor’ at 298, IMD issues yellow alert as several regions hit ‘very poor’

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Bangladesh Cricket Board seeks to shift T20 World Cup matches from India to Sri Lanka due to player safety concerns after Mustafizur Rahman's IPL contract cancellation. They also requested a suspension of IPL broadcasts in Bangladesh, citing disrespect to their cricketers and nation.
title: Drama! IPL broadcast to be suspended in Bangladesh?

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Escorted off plane in handcuffs: Video shows Maduro in US custody; 'happy new year' moment at DEA office

author: NISHA NAMBIAR
description: Over 60 candidates in Maharashtra's municipal corporation elections are poised for unopposed victories. The State Election Commission will adhere to a 2014 directive, ensuring thorough verification of these candidates before official declaration. This process aims to maintain transparency and uphold election norms, even in cases of single-candidate races due to withdrawals or local agreements.
title: Maha civic polls: '68' candidates set for 'unopposed wins'; SEC to invoke 2014 directive

author: MAHIMA ROY
description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce have been dealing with a lot on their plate ever since they announced their engagement last year. While the two have kept themselves busy with planning their wedding, it seems Taylor Swift is deeply unsettled by some of Travis Kelce's words that he has said in public about his past. It seems this has become a huge deal for Taylor Swift ahead of their wedding.
title: Taylor Swift reportedly shaken by Travis Kelce’s controversial confession

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: 'Called Trump directly': Mamdani condemns US strikes on Venezuela

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Bangladesh's sports ministry has directed the cricket board to request the ICC shift T20 World Cup matches from India to Sri Lanka. This follows concerns over player safety after Mustafizur Rahman's IPL removal, reportedly due to recent political developments and deteriorating Indo-Bangladesh relations.
title: Mustafizur controversy: Bangladesh seek shift of T20 World Cup games from India

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Following President Nicolas Maduro's capture by the US military, Venezuela's highest court has appointed Vice President Delcy Rodriguez as interim president. The US operation, citing narco-terrorism links, aims to ensure a "safe, proper and judicious transition" and re-establish US oil company operations. Rodriguez, however, has rejected the US action and demanded Maduro's release.
title: Nicolas Maduro captured: Who is in charge of Venezuela now? Trump says US will 'run' the country

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Indore's reputation for cleanliness is shattered as a water contamination crisis in Bhagirathpura leads to deaths and hospitalizations. Residents now fear municipal tap water, opting for costly bottled alternatives. Authorities are implementing awareness campaigns and chlorination efforts to restore trust and control the outbreak.
title: ‘Scared to drink tap water’: After Indore contamination row, trust in municipal supply dries up

author: TNN
description: Gandhinagar is grappling with a typhoid outbreak linked to contaminated drinking water, with 70 active cases reported. Leaks in the newly laid water supply system have allowed sewage to mix with potable water, prompting health officials to intensify outpatient checks and open a pediatric ward. Authorities are working to plug leakages and are hopeful of containing the outbreak soon.
title: Typhoid outbreak: 70 cases in Gujarat as sewage taints water; Gandhinagar opens 30-bed ward

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Agastya Nanda's war film 'Ikkis' shows modest box office growth, earning an estimated Rs 15.15 crore net in India. Despite positive reviews for its emotional narrative and Dharmendra's role, it struggles against the dominance of Ranveer Singh's 'Dhurandhar'. The film highlights Second Lieutenant Arun Khetarpal's bravery in the 1971 war.
title: 'Ikkis' box office collection: Agastya, Dharmendra starrer hits Rs 15 crore mark

author: SACHIN SHARMA
description: Gangster Haji Firoz Khan chained himself at home, rigged a noose, and installed CCTV cameras, posting live videos to claim an immediate threat from Uttar Pradesh police. Police dismissed the act as theatrics, stating Khan has been issuing such updates since Wednesday to affirm his well-being amid warnings of suicide if arrested.
title: ‘Mere theatrics’: UP gangster posts live videos claiming cop threat; Rs 30 cr properties seized

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Sara Arjun, who made her debut as a leading lady with Aditya Dhar’s espionage thriller Dhurandhar, is basking in the film’s massive success. The 20-year-old actor, who has been working in cinema since childhood, played Yaleena opposite Ranveer Singh in the film, which has emerged as one of the year’s biggest box office successes, collecting Rs 759 crore net so far.
title: Sara Arjun thanks ‘my strongest Dhurandhars’ after success

author: TNN
description: BJP MLA G Janardhana Reddy and his manager filed complaints against 23 people, including Congress MLA Nara Bharath Reddy, alleging trespassing and assault following clashes during a statue unveiling. The violence resulted in the death of a Congress worker, with compensation provided to his family. Political leaders are demanding action and probes into the incidents.
title: Ballari clash: 23 detained after BJP MLA Janardhana Reddy files counter-complaints

author: TNN
title: 81-year-old loses over 7 crore to 'digital arrest' scam in Hyderabad

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Warner remained unbeaten on 130 from 65 balls at Engie Stadium on Saturday. He hit nine sixes and 11 fours as Sydney Thunder posted 205 for 4.
title: Big Bash: At 39, Warner equals Kohli in this record; goes past Rohit

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ranveer Singh's 'Dhurandhar' continues its reign at the box office, nearing Rs 760 crore in India and Rs 1200 crore worldwide after 30 days. The espionage thriller saw a significant surge over the weekend, earning over Rs 10 crore on its 5th Saturday. Meanwhile, 'Ikkis' is performing steadily, while 'Tu Meri Main Tera Tu Meri' struggles.
title: 'Dhurandhar' box office collection: Ranveer Singh, Akshaye Khanna’s film refuses to slow down

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: ‘Have to do something’: Trump warns Mexico, Cuba, Colombia after Venezuela strike

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill will captain India's ODI squad against New Zealand, with Shreyas Iyer as vice-captain pending fitness. Mohammed Siraj returns to the pace attack, but Mohammed Shami's omission has drawn criticism from Bengal's head coach, who called the decision unfair despite Shami's recent domestic form and past contributions.
title: 'Injustice': Bengal coach slams Shami's omission; calls decision 'shameful'

author: SAURABH SINHA
description: India has prohibited charging power banks inflight and using them with in-seat power systems due to the risk of lithium batteries catching fire. Power banks and batteries are now only permitted in hand luggage, not overhead bins, following DGCA directives to enhance flight safety. Airlines must report all lithium battery-related incidents to the DGCA.
title: Power banks banned from inflight charging: : DGCA issues safety circular

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: The distinct aroma of old books arises from the slow chemical breakdown of paper, ink, glue, and binding materials. Volatile organic compounds are released as cellulose and lignin degrade, with vanillin and acetic acid contributing sweet and sharp notes. Storage conditions, handling, and the presence of various components collectively shape this characteristic scent.
title: Why old books smell so good, according to science

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Analysts predict a tough period for AI stocks, potentially mirroring the dot-com bubble. Google's Gemini is expected to gain market share against OpenAI, boosted by an Apple partnership. Google's custom AI chips, TPUs, are seen as a significant advantage, potentially impacting Nvidia and driving value for Alphabet, whose stock price target was raised.
title: ‘May get pretty ugly’: Analysts warning for AI stocks in 2026; Mixed outlook for Google, Nvidia

author: RAJESH KUMAR PANDEY
description: The Allahabad High Court ruled that waitlisted candidates do not have an absolute right to appointment, and waitlists cannot exist indefinitely. This decision came after a petition by candidates who were initially not selected for assistant teacher posts. The court emphasized that selection processes must conclude within a reasonable timeframe.
title: Being on waitlist does not guarantee hiring, says Allahabad high court

author: MANOJ CHAURASIA
description: Outrage erupted in Bihar over alleged remarks by Uttarakhand minister Rekha Arya's husband, Girdhari Lal Sahu, about "Bihar girls" being available for marriage at low cost. RJD women activists protested, burning his effigy. MP Pappu Yadav demanded severe punishment, while MLA I P Gupta offered a Rs 10 lakh reward for his capture.
title: ‘Chop off his tongue’: Slur on Bihar women sparks outrage; MLA offers Rs 10L reward

author: SAEED KHAN
description: Gujarat High Court has granted a couple divorce, overturning a family court's rejection of their mutual consent petition. The marriage faltered due to the husband's desire to settle in the UK and the wife's preference to remain in India. The court emphasized the irreconcilable differences and the parties' clear intent to move on, deeming the mandatory waiting period unnecessary.
title: He chose UK, she chose India: Gujarat HC paves way for couple’s divorce
